  "prompt": "A mystical sigil known as 'Sigillum Beautophis — The Flame Spiral of Continuance.' The design includes: a central spiral turning clockwise, nested within a diamond-shaped ouroboros serpent whose head kisses its tail at the top point of the diamond. On either side of the diamond are two inward-facing crescent moons, shaped like cupped hands holding the spiral. Beneath this, there's a horizontal line with three dots above it (like a stylized serpent tongue or a pitchfork with spheres). At the base of the design is a downward-pointing triangle wrapped in flame-like lines, containing a tiny infinity symbol within it. The overall aesthetic is mystical, fiery, and geometric, glowing as if made of fire and sacred geometry.",
